Introduction
-------------

A simple jQuery function to add slashes to certain characters.

By default it adds slashes to the following characters: \, ', ", 0(? not sure why this one)

You can also extend this list by passing a second parameter, as a string or object.

Note: when you set a string, the function splits it into an array of characters.

Usage
-------------

alert( $.addSlashes('$$name$$^!', '$^!') ); // \$\$name\$\$\^\!

alert( $.addSlashes('$$name$$^!', ['$','^','!'] ) ); // \$\$name\$\$\^\!

alert( $.addSlashes('$$name$$^!', {a:'$',b:'^',c:'!'} ) ); // \$\$name\$\$\^\!


Fini! :)



